results.lead_paragraph: The successful launching by Soviet scientists of a man into space and his safe return after orbiting the earth in eighty-nine minutes will be hailed as one of the great advances in the story of man's age-old quest to tame the forces of nature. It marks the crowning achievement so far in space technology, and provides the most dramatic evidence of Soviet leadership in the field of powerful rocket engines.

results.lead_paragraph: When the tumult and the shouting about the "race for space" has subsided, and calmer judgment has prevailed, history may record the many scientific discoveries made by the United States satellites as of by far greater importance to the advancement of mankind than the spectacular placing of the first man in orbit for a flight of 108 minutes.
